(b) Standard: minimum necessary. 
 (1) Minimum necessary applies.   When
using o r discl osing prote cted he alth
informa tion or wh en reques ting p rotected
health  informa tion fro m anoth er covered
entity, a covered entity must make reasona ble
efforts to  limit p rotected he alth inf ormati on to
the mini mum nece ssary  to acco mplish the
intended pu rpose of the use, disclosure, or
request.  
(2) Minimum necessary does not apply.  This requirement does not ap ply to:
(i) Di sclos ures t o or r eques ts by a  healt h
care pr ovide r for treat ment;
(ii)  U ses o r discl osure s made t o the
individua l, as pe rmitte d under p aragr aph
(a)(1 )(i) o f this s ectio n or as  requir ed by
paragr aph (a)( 2)(i) of this  sectio n;
(iii)  U ses o r discl osure s made p ursuant
to an auth orization unde r § 164.508;
(iv) D isclo sures  made to  the Se creta ry in
accord ance w ith subpar t C of pa rt 160 of  this
